OL,6,F"Well after the Budget, the answer
OL,7,Fwe're hearing from so many firms is
OL,8,Fstill 'not yet'."
OL,10,FLabour made economic growth a central
OL,11,Fpart of its pitch to voters in the
OL,12,Fgeneral election, and has repeatedly
OL,13,Fpledged to help boost business
OL,14,Finvestment since entering Government.
OL,16,FIn the October Budget, Chancellor
OL,17,FRachel Reeves announced a nearly #70
OL,18,Fbillion uplift in public spending,
OL,19,Fpartly funded by sharp increases in
OL,20,Fbusiness taxes such as employer
OL,21,Fnational insurance contributions.
