OL,6,FLabour also raised the minimum wage,
OL,7,Fin a move praised by workers' groups
OL,8,Fand unions, but which businesses have
OL,9,Fsaid will force them to pass on some
OL,10,Fcosts to consumers, hire fewer people
OL,11,For make less profit.
OL,13,FIn her speech, Ms Newton-Smith will
OL,14,Fpoint to a recent survey by the body
OL,15,Fwhich found almost two-thirds of
OL,16,Fcompanies think the Budget will damage
OL,17,FUK investment.
